This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and information extraction, which are typically covered under the Computer Science sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also uses neural models for training, which falls under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with large datasets and uses parsing techniques, which are covered under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with extracting implicit relations, which is a task that falls under the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
